---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '~/lib/siteConfig'
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`About — ${SITE_CONFIG.name}`}
  description={`What ${SITE_CONFIG.name} is and how it fits in the oriz family.`}
>
  <header class="container-prose page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">{SITE_CONFIG.name}</a> / About</p>
    <h1>About {SITE_CONFIG.name}</h1>
  </header>

  <article class="container-prose prose">
    <p class="lede">
      <strong>{SITE_CONFIG.name}</strong> — {SITE_CONFIG.tagline}.
    </p>

    <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
    <p>
      Most online financial calculators in India are wrappers around a single
      formula glued to a lead-capture form. {SITE_CONFIG.name} flips that:
      the math is the product. Each calculator shows you the formula it used,
      the assumptions it made, and the year-by-year breakdown when one exists.
      No sign-up, no &ldquo;talk to an advisor&rdquo; popups, no affiliate
      redirects between you and the answer.
    </p>

    <h2>What it covers</h2>
    <p>
      SIP, lumpsum, step-up SIP, SWP, and goal-based investment planning.
      Home, car, personal, and education loan EMIs with full amortization.
      FD, RD, PPF, NPS, NSC, SSY. Take-home pay, HRA exemption, gratuity,
      leave encashment, GST. CAGR, XIRR, FIRE, inflation impact. Calculators
      get added when the math is unambiguous and the inputs are commonly
      asked.
    </p>

    <h2>What it is not</h2>
    <p>
      Not investment advice. Not a SEBI-registered advisor. Not a place to
      open an account, take a loan, or buy insurance. Outputs are mathematical
      projections from your inputs, nothing more — see the
      <a href="/legal/disclaimer/">disclaimer</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Part of oriz</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE_CONFIG.name} is one of nine static sites under
      <a href="https://oriz.in">oriz.in</a> — built by Chirag Singhal, deployed
      to Cloudflare's edge, sharing one Firebase sign-in across the family. See
      the <a href="https://oriz.in">oriz hub</a> for the full lineup, or the
      <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> if you spot something wrong.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-head { padding-block: 3rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .eyebrow { color: var(--color-fg-muted); font-size: 0.8125rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  .eyebrow a { color: var(--color-fg-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  h1 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 0; }
  .prose { padding-block: 2.5rem 4rem; color: var(--color-prose); line-height: 1.75; font-size: 1.0625rem; }
  .prose .lede { font-size: 1.1875rem; color: var(--color-fg); margin: 0 0 2rem; }
  .prose h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-fg); margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .prose a { color: var(--color-accent); }
</style>
